WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:06.000
This is how you pick a move. You draw it.

2
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:15.000
The canvas is a timeline. Left to right is the time of day.
Up and down is the size of the move, in basis points.

3
00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:25.000
Drag a box over the window you trade. Its left edge and
width set when the move starts and how long it runs.

4
00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:35.000
The top and bottom set the size band. The dashed cutoff
line is how long you keep watching it.

5
00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:45.000
Let go, and the stats compute on release. Win rate, how
often the structure held, and the typical move size.

6
00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:56.000
Set your cashflow target up top. That's the move you're
actually paid for, in percent.

7
00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:07.000
Switch from Exact to Region and it scans every box inside
your shape, then hands you the strongest one.

8
00:01:07.000 --> 00:01:18.000
Turn signals on and drop a second box, the violet one,
somewhere before your trade.

9
00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:30.000
Now it measures the timing. When that signal fires first,
does your win rate actually lift? The panel shows the
before and after.

10
00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:42.000
Filter by what the signal was doing at your entry, and
rank the setups by how much lift they add.

11
00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:51.000
Geometry in, edge out. That's the whole idea behind
picking a move.
